19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>Piracy in deep space!</i>

20
00:00:20,775 --> 00:00:25,655
<i>Infamous outlaw Hondo Ohnaka attacks
a Jedi transport carrying six younglings,</i>

21
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:28,282
<i>who just received their lightsaber crystals.</i>

22
00:00:28,616 --> 00:00:30,409
<i>So rare are these crystals,</i>

23
00:00:30,451 --> 00:00:34,747
<i>that Hondo knows he can sell them
on the black market for a small fortune.</i>

24
00:00:34,956 --> 00:00:37,291
<i>In a desperate attempt
to save the younglings,</i>

25
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:40,920
<i>Ahsoka Tano is captured by Hondo
and his pirate horde.</i>

26
00:00:41,462 --> 00:00:46,300
<i>Now, with a damaged ship,
the younglings are stranded and alone.</i>

27
00:00:51,806 --> 00:00:54,934
This is the <i>Crucible.</i>
Calling the Republic fleet.

28
00:00:54,976 --> 00:00:57,979
Come in, please. We need help.

29
00:00:58,187 --> 00:01:00,690
<i>This is General Kenobi.
We have your transmission.</i>

30
00:01:00,815 --> 00:01:02,316
The General Kenobi?

31
00:01:05,820 --> 00:01:09,156
The pirate Hondo has attacked
and severely damaged our ship

32
00:01:09,198 --> 00:01:11,826
and taken our chaperone, Ahsoka Tano.

33
00:01:11,951 --> 00:01:14,620
I'm dispatching Commander Cody
to bring you back.

34
00:01:14,662 --> 00:01:16,622
We shall deal with Hondo on Florrum.

35
00:01:16,664 --> 00:01:18,207
<i>Will Ahsoka be all right?</i>

36
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:22,169
Hondo would be even more of a fool
than I think he is to hurt her.

37
00:01:22,211 --> 00:01:24,964
Once we've picked you up,
we'll focus on rescuing Ahsoka.

38
00:01:25,006 --> 00:01:27,717
But we could help Ahsoka a lot
sooner than you can.

39
00:01:28,175 --> 00:01:30,303
<i>You have shown great bravery
but these pirates...</i>

40
00:01:30,344 --> 00:01:33,180
It was us who managed
to drive them from the ship.

41
00:01:33,306 --> 00:01:37,685
You will not jeopardize your safety
trying to be heroes, understood?

42
00:01:37,977 --> 00:01:39,353
<i>Yes, Master.</i>

43
00:01:40,688 --> 00:01:43,649
Their coordinates put them
dangerously close to Florrum.

44
00:01:43,691 --> 00:01:45,526
I do not want them getting any ideas.

45
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:47,194
You will need to leave quickly, Cody.

46
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,363
Sir, enemy fleet's
coming out of hyperspace!

47
00:02:02,335 --> 00:02:04,879
Battle stations! Launch all fighters!

48
00:02:05,004 --> 00:02:08,257
Cody, looks like you're staying
here for now.

49
00:03:29,672 --> 00:03:30,840
What do you think?

50
00:03:31,674 --> 00:03:33,843
I think you've finished your lightsaber.

51
00:03:34,343 --> 00:03:36,512
Doesn't mean you know how to use it.

52
00:03:36,637 --> 00:03:39,932
Well, if you hurry up with yours,
maybe we could find out.

53
00:03:46,647 --> 00:03:49,483
I'll finish mine when I'm ready.

54
00:03:52,194 --> 00:03:55,156
Seeing as how our rescue party
has forgotten us,

55
00:03:55,197 --> 00:03:56,991
you'll have plenty of time.

56
00:03:59,452 --> 00:04:01,245
They probably just got delayed.

57
00:04:02,997 --> 00:04:07,084
Delayed? Ahsoka needs our help
and we're sitting around like children.

58
00:04:07,501 --> 00:04:09,086
We are children.

59
00:04:09,336 --> 00:04:11,672
I vote we mount a rescue mission.

60
00:04:13,841 --> 00:04:15,801
Gungi is with me. Byph?

61
00:04:18,846 --> 00:04:20,806
That's three votes for and...

62
00:04:20,848 --> 00:04:22,516
One against.

63
00:04:25,519 --> 00:04:26,854
Perfect timing.

64
00:04:26,979 --> 00:04:28,856
There's a problem with the ship.

65
00:04:28,981 --> 00:04:30,357
What kind of problem?

66
00:04:30,483 --> 00:04:34,695
Breaking away from the pirate ship
ruptured the entire filtering system.

67
00:04:34,987 --> 00:04:36,030
What does that mean?

68
00:04:36,113 --> 00:04:38,282
It means, she's venting coolant

69
00:04:38,365 --> 00:04:40,993
and if we don't land soon,
the engines will explode.

70
00:04:41,035 --> 00:04:43,370
We'll have to land and let the system reset.

71
00:04:43,496 --> 00:04:46,373
Then it's settled.
If we stay out here, we'll die.

72
00:04:46,499 --> 00:04:50,377
We go to Florrum, let the engines cool,
and rescue Ahsoka.

73
00:04:52,963 --> 00:04:55,007
A rescue mission?

74
00:05:21,575 --> 00:05:24,411
It would be wise
if you would let me go.

75
00:05:24,495 --> 00:05:27,498
No, it would be unprofitable
if I would let you go,

76
00:05:27,581 --> 00:05:31,669
and why would I do something
as shortsighted as that?

77
00:05:32,169 --> 00:05:34,004
If you don't let me go,

78
00:05:34,088 --> 00:05:37,591
you will wish you had been born
a protocol droid.

79
00:05:38,342 --> 00:05:40,010
Sometimes I do anyway.

80
00:05:40,094 --> 00:05:45,224
But you are really in no position
to make threats, young lady.

81
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:48,769
You look stressed. Are you thirsty?

82
00:05:48,853 --> 00:05:50,563
A drink, perhaps?

83
00:05:53,774 --> 00:05:57,695
Sorry, but I do not like to share.

84
00:06:43,282 --> 00:06:44,950
Our forces are being overrun.

85
00:06:44,992 --> 00:06:47,161
The droids are sending out
boarding parties.

86
00:06:47,953 --> 00:06:50,915
We must get to the main hangar
to repel them.

87
00:07:38,379 --> 00:07:41,882
We're being overrun ! Push forward!

88
00:08:01,735 --> 00:08:03,070
Kenobi...

89
00:08:12,413 --> 00:08:14,039
You'll regret that.

90
00:08:22,756 --> 00:08:24,591
Florrum.

91
00:08:30,597 --> 00:08:32,933
Guess we're in the right place.

92
00:08:51,118 --> 00:08:54,788
Artoo, finish reassembling
Master Huyang, will you?

93
00:08:55,914 --> 00:08:57,791
I hate to see him like this.

94
00:08:59,293 --> 00:09:01,211
Ganodi, you stay with the ship.

95
00:09:01,295 --> 00:09:03,422
And who put you in charge?

96
00:09:03,464 --> 00:09:05,549
We're going to need to make quick escape.

97
00:09:05,632 --> 00:09:08,719
And you are the only one that
had flight simulator training at the temple.

98
00:09:08,927 --> 00:09:11,638
Oh. Seeing as you put it like that...

99
00:09:42,169 --> 00:09:45,005
I don't see anything, there's no one.

100
00:09:46,757 --> 00:09:49,093
Are we sure we even landed
near their base?

101
00:09:49,176 --> 00:09:52,179
Well, we couldn't land too close, could we?

102
00:09:52,304 --> 00:09:57,518
My scanner's indicating
a strong power source, that way.

103
00:09:58,018 --> 00:10:00,020
It must be their base.

104
00:10:00,145 --> 00:10:04,358
You have no idea how we are going
to get inside and find Ahsoka, do you?

105
00:10:04,483 --> 00:10:05,859
I'm working on it.

106
00:10:07,861 --> 00:10:09,696
Byph is right, we better get moving.

107
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,032
We'll figure out a strategy on the way.

108
00:10:25,712 --> 00:10:28,465
You know the Republic
won't pay a ransom for me,

109
00:10:28,549 --> 00:10:30,551
and the Separatists can't be trusted.

110
00:10:30,634 --> 00:10:32,553
They'll betray you and kill us both.

111
00:10:32,678 --> 00:10:34,721
Yes, I know this, my dear.

112
00:10:34,805 --> 00:10:38,058
The Separatists are no friends of mine.

113
00:10:38,183 --> 00:10:42,229
Don't ask me why,
but Dooku holds such a grudge against me

114
00:10:42,354 --> 00:10:47,234
since our little "I-held-him-hostage" affair.

115
00:10:47,276 --> 00:10:52,698
The truth is, I have my sights set
on more nefarious criminals than I,

116
00:10:52,739 --> 00:10:56,410
a businessman,
who will pay handsomely for a Jedi.

117
00:10:56,451 --> 00:10:59,371
A female Jedi at that!

118
00:10:59,413 --> 00:11:01,415
You don't scare me, Hondo.

119
00:11:02,875 --> 00:11:07,212
Oh, by the way, they don't care
if you're dead or alive.

120
00:11:07,754 --> 00:11:12,092
I mean, I prefer alive, less messy.

121
00:11:12,134 --> 00:11:16,889
But I find my moods
so changeable these days.

122
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:25,731
-General ! The fuel barrel.
-Right!

123
00:11:36,283 --> 00:11:38,952
Fall back! Fall back!

124
00:11:41,496 --> 00:11:45,167
This is General Kenobi.
Abandon ship. Abandon ship.

125
00:11:45,292 --> 00:11:47,002
<i>Sir, shouldn't we stay and fight.</i>

126
00:11:47,127 --> 00:11:48,420
<i>We can't lose the ship now.</i>

127
00:11:48,462 --> 00:11:51,632
Cody, the ship is already lost.
We must face it.

128
00:11:51,757 --> 00:11:54,801
But you and I are going to give Grievous
a little parting gift.

129
00:12:13,695 --> 00:12:15,656
A ship? What kind?

130
00:12:16,531 --> 00:12:20,994
The side of the ship says
"Preigo's Traveling World of Wonder."

131
00:12:21,495 --> 00:12:24,039
They're a traveling carnival act!

132
00:12:27,376 --> 00:12:30,337
Faster, you lazy creatures! Faster!

133
00:12:30,379 --> 00:12:33,799
Old Hondo will be furious if we are late.

134
00:12:33,882 --> 00:12:35,509
You hear me?

135
00:12:53,193 --> 00:12:54,528
Hey!

136
00:12:54,653 --> 00:12:58,991
You there! What... What are you doing?
I said faster, not stop.

137
00:13:02,577 --> 00:13:05,539
Sir, are we to understand

138
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:08,041
you are on your way
to the pirate stronghold?

139
00:13:08,083 --> 00:13:10,043
Yes, what's it to you?

140
00:13:10,085 --> 00:13:13,046
Who are you? How did you get out here?

141
00:13:13,171 --> 00:13:15,882
Sir, our ship crashed
and we've been stranded,

142
00:13:16,008 --> 00:13:19,011
but our misfortune is to your benefit.

143
00:13:19,344 --> 00:13:23,557
Oh, really?
And how is that, my curious friend?

144
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:26,560
We are...

145
00:13:26,685 --> 00:13:29,688
Acrobats, entertainers!

146
00:13:31,273 --> 00:13:35,068
We would love to join your act and
travel with you to your next destination.

147
00:13:35,193 --> 00:13:40,407
Really? All of you wish to join my act?
Right.

148
00:13:40,532 --> 00:13:42,784
You would like to come with us

149
00:13:42,909 --> 00:13:47,122
when we go to entertain Hondo
and his pirate horde?

150
00:13:47,247 --> 00:13:49,916
Very much so, yes.

151
00:13:50,417 --> 00:13:51,543
Oh no, no, no. I...

152
00:13:51,585 --> 00:13:55,088
I'm sorry, the pirates are
an unforgiving audience,

153
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:57,549
I couldn't possibly...

154
00:13:57,632 --> 00:14:00,093
What... How did you...

155
00:14:00,218 --> 00:14:01,970
Oh my, my.

156
00:14:03,638 --> 00:14:06,099
Artists! True artists!

157
00:14:06,183 --> 00:14:10,020
Young man,
how many of these tricks can you do?

158
00:14:13,523 --> 00:14:15,108
How many do you want?

159
00:14:15,609 --> 00:14:19,446
Oh ! Welcome to the show!

160
00:14:35,128 --> 00:14:37,506
General, we have secured the ship.

161
00:14:37,631 --> 00:14:38,965
Excellent.

162
00:14:39,007 --> 00:14:44,471
Waste no time and get me every last piece
of information from the data banks.

163
00:14:45,180 --> 00:14:48,475
<i>General Grievous, you have defeated me</i>

164
00:14:48,517 --> 00:14:52,312
<i>and taken control
of my ship, congratulations.</i>

165
00:14:52,396 --> 00:14:56,483
<i>However, if you are watching this message
that means I'm boarding an escape pod</i>

166
00:14:56,525 --> 00:14:59,361
<i>and shall soon be safely away
from the ship,</i>

167
00:14:59,486 --> 00:15:01,321
<i>which is about to self-destruct.</i>

168
00:15:01,738 --> 00:15:04,574
<i>General Grievous, you have defeated me...</i>

169
00:15:15,669 --> 00:15:17,003
Sir.

170
00:15:21,508 --> 00:15:24,177
Wait! Wait! What are you doing?

171
00:15:24,678 --> 00:15:26,721
-Uh-oh.
-Uh-oh!

172
00:15:44,406 --> 00:15:47,701
I'm afraid the younglings
are now on their own.

173
00:16:19,566 --> 00:16:22,569
Preigo.

174
00:16:28,241 --> 00:16:31,578
You better know what you are doing
because I don't see Ahsoka.

175
00:16:31,661 --> 00:16:32,913
Patience.

176
00:16:33,121 --> 00:16:39,127
I, Preigo, your humble servant,
have searched far and wide,

177
00:16:39,252 --> 00:16:42,422
oh, illustrious plunderer of the universe,

178
00:16:42,464 --> 00:16:46,259
and found you
a most special entertainment.

179
00:16:46,801 --> 00:16:48,428
Good!

180
00:16:48,512 --> 00:16:53,350
I would hate to be forced to
cut off their heads like I did your last act.

181
00:16:53,433 --> 00:16:54,976
You remember those guys?

182
00:16:59,648 --> 00:17:03,818
You are a brave man
to come before me again.

183
00:17:04,152 --> 00:17:06,655
Look! He has Ahsoka's lightsabers!

184
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:07,822
I'll get them!

185
00:17:08,657 --> 00:17:10,450
Where is my Jedi?

186
00:17:10,534 --> 00:17:12,994
I would hate for her to miss the show.

187
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:16,456
Which I'm hoping will be better
than last time.

188
00:17:17,832 --> 00:17:20,961
Excellent! Let the show begin!

189
00:17:21,044 --> 00:17:22,963
Yes, of course.

190
00:17:23,713 --> 00:17:28,093
<i>May I present the Animal Instincts.</i>

191
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:37,352
Oh, no.

192
00:17:38,311 --> 00:17:40,146
I love a kiddie act.

193
00:18:09,593 --> 00:18:11,219
What is this business?

194
00:18:11,595 --> 00:18:15,974
I believe he wants you to be a part
of the next stunt.

195
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,935
Ho-ho! Does he now?

196
00:18:19,019 --> 00:18:20,604
Come with us.

197
00:18:22,355 --> 00:18:23,773
Which one of you said that?

198
00:18:26,151 --> 00:18:31,281
I may not be as young as I once was,
but I'm older.

199
00:18:33,116 --> 00:18:35,035
Stand right here.

200
00:18:35,118 --> 00:18:37,662
Who wants to see Hondo's moves?

201
00:18:37,746 --> 00:18:39,789
Talk to me!

202
00:19:10,779 --> 00:19:12,489
You guys shouldn't be here.

203
00:19:12,572 --> 00:19:15,700
Don't worry, we have a plan.

204
00:19:15,784 --> 00:19:17,160
I think.

205
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,961
I'm flying!

206
00:19:28,338 --> 00:19:30,131
What the...
Oh no, no, no, no!

207
00:19:30,215 --> 00:19:31,841
Not again ! Oh!

208
00:19:38,807 --> 00:19:40,975
Well, that was a good act!

209
00:19:43,228 --> 00:19:45,480
It's those bleeding Jedi kids.

210
00:19:45,563 --> 00:19:48,233
Wait... What? The children are Jedi?

211
00:19:48,316 --> 00:19:49,401
Oh!

212
00:19:57,951 --> 00:19:59,953
Get to those speeders!

213
00:20:03,623 --> 00:20:05,250
We've gotta run for it!

214
00:20:06,042 --> 00:20:08,878
Those blasted kids
have screwed everything up!

215
00:20:08,962 --> 00:20:10,797
Hondo's going to kill us!

216
00:20:24,602 --> 00:20:26,646
Quick! Get to that speeder!

217
00:20:34,404 --> 00:20:35,655
Get us out of here!

218
00:20:42,287 --> 00:20:43,788
What is going on?

219
00:20:44,539 --> 00:20:46,416
Where's my Jedi?

220
00:20:46,499 --> 00:20:49,127
Someone stop them ! Hurry, Gwarm!

221
00:20:49,502 --> 00:20:51,045
Get after them!

222
00:20:51,212 --> 00:20:52,756
Ah.

223
00:20:52,839 --> 00:20:54,674
I know how you feel.

224
00:20:55,216 --> 00:20:58,052
You lost your master,

225
00:20:58,136 --> 00:21:01,347
and I lost my Jedi.

226
00:21:02,140 --> 00:21:03,308
Ugh.

227
00:21:14,944 --> 00:21:16,029
How do you feel?

228
00:21:16,404 --> 00:21:18,239
Better now.

229
00:21:18,698 --> 00:21:23,578
I could pretend to be angry
but you were all very brave, thank you.

230
00:21:24,204 --> 00:21:25,371
We disobeyed orders.

231
00:21:25,830 --> 00:21:27,957
Well, I've learned from my master

232
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:32,629
that sometimes doing the right thing
means bending the rules.

233
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:36,174
Ganodi, come in, please.

234
00:21:36,257 --> 00:21:39,093
Get the ship ready we need to take off.

235
00:21:39,117 --> 00:21:44,117
http://hiqve.com/

